        public void connect(OnServiceReadyListener onServiceReadyListener)
        Description copied from interface: ProximityManagerContract
        Connects to backing ProximityService. This needs to be done before first calling ProximityManagerContract.startScanning().
        Specified by:
        connect in interface ProximityManagerContract
        Parameters:
        onServiceReadyListener - Listener used to specify if ProximityManager has successfully connected to backing service. This means that all necessary Android permissions have been granted and ProximityManager is ready to start scanning.

        Description copied from interface: ProximityManagerContract
